  What's New Since 1.02,"
      What's New Since 1.02      

This topic describes interface and language changes since FoxPro version 1.02.


       Interface Additions       
         and Enhancements        

Project Manager  New
	Projects keep track of all programs, screens, menus, reports, labels, libraries, queries, formats and any other files required to create an application.  

RQBE  New 
	RQBE (Relational Query By Example) lets you create complex single- or multi-table queries (i.e., SQL SELECT commands) using the simple, intuitive RQBE window.  

	Beginners can access databases without programming, experienced users can create complex queries to put in programs, and end-users can create queries or reports with ease.

Screen Builder  New
	This power tool gives you a new way to design screens.  Not only do you define the objects to be included on the screen, but you include code to be executed.  

Menu Builder  New
	This power tool gives you an easy, interactive way to design custom menus, and a Quick Menu feature for even faster designs.  

Printer Driver Support  New
	You can now specify a printer driver through the Printer Setup... option on the File menu popup, or through the Report Writer and Label Designer.  You can even create your own printer driver!

And Even More...
	Enhancements too numerous to mention have been made to the FoxPro interface -- new features, new dialogs, new capabilities.  For example:

	- 	Context-sensitive help for the interface, with See Also and Lookup buttons.
  
	- 	A keyboard macros editor lets you create and edit keyboard macros.

	- 	Report variables can now be created within a report. 

	- 	Text editor enhancements like cut and paste, and automatic continuation of hanging indents.

	- 	Windows you can minimize and dock.

	- 	You can import many more file types using the Append From dialog. 

	- 	You can specify style and type of text in labels and in Reports.

	- 	The Trace window lets you see your program as it runs, with menu bar access to sophisticated program animation capabilities. 

	- 	You can set one-to-many relationships between databases. 

	- 	An Index dialog lets you create compound or single entry index files.


