     FoxPro Self-Running Demo    

You can start the self-running demo in one of the following ways:

	At the DOS prompt where FoxPro is installed, type FOXPRO DEMO.

	In the FoxPro Command window, type DO DEMO and press Enter.

When you're ready to exit the self-running demo, do one of the following:

	Press Escape.

	Click on the Open Door icon.",General pe
  Patching FoxPro,"
        Patching FoxPro          

From time to time, we enhance FoxPro and make minor corrections to the software, help file, printer driver database, or sample programs.  Most of the time, these enhancements are not significant enough to warrant sending updates to all registered users.  However, it is possible that one of them will be just the improvement you have been waiting for and you may want to get the new version.

We will make patch files for new versions of the software, help file, printer driver database and sample programs available on our forum (FOXFORUM) on CompuServe.  These files will be in Library 5 -- Updates.  Registered users can update their copies of FoxPro by applying the patches (following the directions posted on CompuServe).  

Some files will be complete replacements for files on your system -- others will be patch files that modify your existing files to match the latest version.

To update from a previous revision:

	1.	Back up the version of FoxPro installed on your system.

	2.	Reinstall FoxPro from the latest version of the disks you have.  Do not install any optional pieces (such as the Distribution Kit) at this time.

	3.	Patch your FoxPro following the directions on CompuServe.

	4.	Reinstall any optional products.

	5.	Patch the options products (following the directions on CompuServe) if necessary.

We believe that this innovative method of distributing minor software updates will make it much easier for you to stay current with our latest editions.",General er
 General Topics ,"
          General Topics         

The following topics contain information on customizing and configuring FoxPro, as well as hints and tips on using many of FoxPro's new features.",General
