  Running Under DESQview,"
       Running FoxPro 2.0        
    with QuarterDeck DESQview    

In DESQview, the Change a Program menu presents two screens that provide information to DESQview about FoxPro 2.0.
   
First Screen (Basic Information):
   
Memory Size:	400K (minimum size requirement for FoxPro 2.0 execution)

Program:		FOXPRO.EXE; FOXPROX.EXE; FOXPROL.EXE or FOXPROLX.EXE (if the .EXE extension is not provided, an additional copy of COMMAND.COM is loaded for execution)

Parameters:		Any allowable FoxPro parameters (e.g., -e)

Directory:		Path to the location of the FoxPro executables listed on the Program option line (e.g., C:\FOXPRO2)

Options
	
Writes directly to screen: [Y]
	FoxPro does it own screen display routines and therefore requires this option to be turned on to prevent ""screen bleeding"" outside of a resized or zoomed DESQview window.

Displays graphics information: [N]

Virtualize text/graphics (Y,N,T): [N]
	This option is 80386-specific and allows FoxPro to run in a small DESQview window, if specified.  Note that the screen scrolls incorrectly until you Zoom the small DESQview window.

Uses Serial Ports: [Y]
	If your programs uses the serial ports (to dial a phone number via a modem, for example), be sure that this option is set on.

Second Screen (Advanced Options)
		
System Memory (in K): [ ]
	This is DESQview system memory. It is best to leave this option 0 and let DESQview determine what it requires.
 
Max Program Memory Size (in K): [800]
	This increases the amount of memory FoxPro 2.0 gets above the amount specified in the Memory Size option on the first screen.  The amount of memory above 640K is made available via DESQview's VIDRAM facility.  FoxPro only gets this memory if it is available at start-up.
	   
Max Expanded Memory Size (in K): [ ]
	The amount of Expanded memory FoxPro 2.0 uses.  This also controls the amount of extended memory the FoxPro Extended version uses.  DESQview respects the setting of EMS size in FoxPro's CONFIG.FP.  Allocate as much Expanded memory as desired:

	0		FoxPro uses no Expanded memory
	
	<value>	FoxPro uses the specified amount of Expanded memory
	
	blank	FoxPro uses all Expanded memory

Text Pages: [1]
	You need to specify 1 text page to be set aside for display memory.
   
Maximum Height			[50]
Maximum Width			[80]
Starting Height			[25]
Starting Width			[80]
Starting Row			[0]
Starting Column			[0]
	To change FoxPro 2.0 display mode from 25 lines to 50 lines, the Height, Width, Row and Column values must be set in DESQview to accommodate window startup mode. If DESQview is in 25 line display mode when FoxPro is selected and you change FoxPro to 50 line mode, DESQview is automatically changed to 50 line mode.  Changing FoxPro changes the DESQview mode automatically, but changing DESQview mode does not automatically change FoxPro's mode.

Allow Close Window command: [N]
	An ""N"" prevents closing of the FoxPro window from DESQview prior to quitting FoxPro.

Uses Math Coprocessor: [Y]
	This should be set to ""Y"".

Uses its own colors: [Y]
	This must be set to yes for the FoxPro color set to be activated.  Otherwise the DESQview color set is initialized.",General cf
  Running Under Windows 3.0,"
       Running FoxPro 2.0        
        under Windows 3.x        

FoxPro 2.0 is NOT a Microsoft Windows 3.0 application.  FoxPro 2.0 can be executed as a ""Non-Windows Application"" in the Windows DOS compatibility box.  Microsoft recommends that you have at least 2 MB of LIM 4.0 EMS memory and that you leave as much disk space free and unfragmented as possible to reduce disk activity.

Windows has three modes of execution: enhanced, real and standard.  For more information, refer to the Windows documentation.  ""Non-Windows Applications"" do not normally need a program information file (PIF) to run, but the following PIF options are recommended for use with FoxPro 2.0.

Standard Options

Program Filename
	FOXPRO.EXE, FOXPROL.EXE
