This trigonometric function returns the arc tangent of <expN>, an angle in radians between -pi/2 and +pi/2.  The <expN> may be any value.

The numeric value returned by ATAN() is in radians; you may convert this value to degrees with the RTOD() function.  The number of decimal places returned by ATAN() is determined by the SET DECIMALS command.


