COMPILE,"
             COMPILE             

COMPILE <file> | <skel>
	[ENCRYPT] [NODEBUG]


Compiles a program file.


Compilation error messages are saved to a text file if SET LOGERRORS is ON when a program is compiled.  SET LOGERRORS ON to save compilation error messages to a text file with the same name as the program being compiled.  The error log file will be given an extension of .ERR.  If SET LOGERRORS is OFF, an error log file isn't created.

