",Command pe
CONTINUE,"
            CONTINUE             

CONTINUE


Continues previous LOCATE command. 


This command is used in conjunction with the LOCATE command to continue the LOCATE operation, skipping to the next record which matches the criteria specified in the LOCATE command.  You may CONTINUE interactively by issuing CONTINUE in the Command window, by choosing Continue from the Record menu popup or by pressing Ctrl+K.

The process of continuing can be repeated until the end of the file is encountered or until the end of the LOCATE <scope> is reached.  If the LOCATE command finds a matching record, RECNO() will return the record number of the matched record, FOUND() will return a value of true (.T.) and EOF() will return a value of false (.F.).

If a match is not found, RECNO() will return the number of records in the database plus one, FOUND() will return the value false (.F.) and EOF() will return the value true (.T.).


         Program Example         

In this example, all customers from Perrysburg are counted and total is displayed.  All matching records are found and counted using LOCATE/CONTINUE combination.

CLOSE ALL
SET TALK OFF
USE customer
STORE 0 TO mcount
LOCATE FOR ALLTRIM(UPPER(city)) = 'PERRYSBURG' 
DO WHILE FOUND()
   mcount = mcount + 1
   CONTINUE
ENDDO
? 'Total customers from Perrysburg: '+ LTRIM(STR(mcount))



See Also:  EOF(), FIND, FOUND(), LOCATE, SEEK

