",Command db fm
COPY STRUCTURE,"
         COPY STRUCTURE          

COPY STRUCTURE TO <file>
	[FIELDS <field list>]
	[[WITH] CDX 
	| [WITH] PRODUCTION]]


Copies database structure to another database. 


FIELDS <field list>
	Specifies fields to be copied to new database.

[WITH] CDX | [WITH] PRODUCTION
	Creates structural index for new database.


         Program Example         

In this example, CUSTOMER database is opened, its structure is copied to file called BACKUP and BACKUP is opened for record input.  FoxPro then appends records from CUSTOMER database.

USE customer
