DTOC(<expD> [, 1])


Converts <expD> to character expression.
Return value - Character


The format in which the date is presented is controlled by the current SET CENTURY and SET DATE options.

1
	Date returned in form suitable for use in indexing.  This can be particularly useful in combination with the TIME() function to maintain a database in time sequence.

	For instance, an order-entry database could be indexed by:

	REPLACE INVDATE WITH DATE(), INVTIME WITH TIME()
	INDEX ON DTOC(INVDATE,1)+INVTIME TO Timeindx

	to allow access to it in time-of-entry sequence.


