The LUPDATE() function returns the date that the currently active database was last updated.  This function is useful when verifying that a particular update procedure takes place on a daily basis.

LUPDATE() returns the last update for the database file in the currently selected work area.  The LUPDATE() of database files opened in other unselected work areas may be checked by including the optional <alias>.  Specify a database alias or work area letter (work area letters A through J for the first ten work areas only) or specify the work area number.  If you specify an alias or work area letter it must be enclosed in single or double quotes.  

<expN> | <expC>
