SET CONFIRM,"
           SET CONFIRM           

SET CONFIRM ON | OFF


Specifies if terminating key must be pressed when exiting field.
Default value - OFF


When SET CONFIRM is OFF and last character in input field is entered, the input operation is automatically terminated.  Cursor moves to next field and bell sounds (if BELL is SET ON).

If CONFIRM is SET ON, user is required to press terminating key (Enter, Tab, etc.) to indicate that input is complete.  

The CONFIRM setting also affects popups and menu bars created with MENU.  If CONFIRM is SET OFF, you may chose option from popup or pad from a menu bar by pressing first letter of option.  

If CONFIRM is SET ON, pressing first letter of option or pad selects option or pad.  To chose option or pad you must press Enter or Spacebar to confirm choice. 

If a popup option or menu bar pad is defined with hot key, the option or pad may be chosen by pressing the corresponding hot key.  SET CONFIRM has no effect upon hot keys.",Command in km
