SET CURRENCY,"
          SET CURRENCY           

SET CURRENCY TO [<expC>]

SET CURRENCY LEFT | RIGHT


Specifies the currency symbol and position.
Default value - ""$""
Default value - LEFT


<expC>
	A one- to nine-character string representing currency symbol. Using SET CURRENCY TO without <expC> resets the currency symbol to the default dollar sign ($).  

LEFT | RIGHT
	Allows you to position currency symbol to left or right of currency value.


             Example             

You can display a different currency symbol ('DM') on both sides of the currency value.  Use PICTURE to display the currency symbol, be sure to include an @ before the dollar sign.

STORE SET('CURRENCY') TO currposit
STORE 1234.56 TO dollaramnt
CLEAR

SET CURRENCY TO 'DM'
@ 2,2 SAY dollaramnt PICTURE '@$99,999.99'

IF currposit = 'LEFT'
	SET CURRENCY RIGHT
ELSE
	SET CURRENCY LEFT
ENDIF
@ 4,2 SAY dollaramnt FUNCTION '$99,999.99'",Command en in
