SET PRINTER,"
           SET PRINTER           

SET PRINTER ON | OFF

SET PRINTER TO 
	[<file> [ADDITIVE] | <port>] 

FoxPro/LAN:

SET PRINTER TO
 	[\\<machine name> 
 	\<printer name> = <dest>]

SET PRINTER TO 
	[\\SPOOLER [\NB]
	  [\F = <expN>] [\B = <banner>]  
	  [\C = <expN>] [\P = <expN>]]
	  [\S = <server>] [\Q = <queue>]


Enables or disables output to printer and specifies output port.
Default value - ON


SET PRINTER ON
	Enables output to printer.  Output formatted with  @ ... SAY is not routed to printer when PRINTER is SET ON.  To direct @ ... SAY commands to printer, use SET DEVICE TO PRINTER.

SET PRINTER OFF
	Disables output to printer.

SET PRINTER TO [<file> [ADDITIVE] | <port>]
	Specify a file or a port where output will be directed.  Include file name to specify disk file to direct output to.  Include keyword ADDITIVE, to append to any existing contents of <file>.  If the ADDITIVE keyword is not included, existing contents of file are overwritten.  

You can also specify port to send output to different local printers.  You can specify one of three parallel ports (LPT1, LPT2 or LPT3) or one of two serial ports (COM1 or COM2).  Use SET PRINTER TO without an argument to reset output to the default DOS PRN print utility.

Default destination for SET PRINTER TO is the DOS PRN print utility.

FoxPro/LAN: 


\\<machine name>\<printername> = <dest>
	First format of network SET PRINTER command spools printer output to a network printer.  <machine name> is  network name assigned to your work station.  Name is assigned by network administrator and must be unique.  <printer name> is name assigned to printer and is also assigned by the network administrator. LPT1, LPT2 or LPT3 is used to identify the destination <dest> of the installed printer.

SET PRINTER TO
	Second format of network SET PRINTER command is specifically designed for printing under Novell Advanced Netware (R) revision 2.00 or higher.  

	Default destination for SET PRINTER TO is the DOS PRN print utility.

SPOOLER
	SPOOLER must be present for compatibility but is ignored - any character string may be substituted.

\NB
	Suppresses printing a banner page (No Banner).

\F = <expN> 
	Specifies form number <expN> (0 to 255) that output should be printed on.

\B = <banner>
	Banner name.  Specifies heading  printed on banner page.  Heading <banner> can be up to 12 characters.  Default heading is your user name.

\C = <expN>
	Specifies number of copies (1 to 255) to be queued to network printer.  Default is 1.

\P = <expN>
	Specifies network printer where output will be sent.  <expN> is a number assigned to printer by network.  Default is 0.

\S = <server>
	Specifies network server printer is attached to where output will be sent.  The <server> name should not be a character expression, i.e. not surrounded by quotation marks.

\Q = <queue>
	Specifies queue name assigned to printer you will be sending output to.  <queue> name should not be character expression, i.e. not surrounded by quotation marks.  



See Also:  PRINTSTATUS(), SYS(6) PRINTER device, SYS(13) Printer status, SYS(102) PRINTER setting

