            SYS(2019)            



Returns the name and location of CONFIG.FP.
Return value - Character


SYS(2019) returns the name and location of the FoxPro CONFIG.FP configuration file.  If a configuration file cannot be located, the null string is returned.

CONFIG.FP is typically located in the directory where FoxPro is started, but may be located elsewhere.  FoxPro first looks for CONFIG.FP in the directory where FoxPro is started.  If CONFIG.FP is not located here, FoxPro then searches the DOS path.

Two options let you tell FoxPro where your configuration file is located and its name (which may differ from CONFIG.FP).  A DOS environmental variable named FOXPROCFG can be created with the DOS SET command.  You can store the location and name of your configuration file in FOXPROCFG. 

You can also use the -C switch when starting FoxPro to designate a configuration file.  Include the location and name of the configuration file immediately after -C.



