WLAST() function returns a logical true if the specified window was active prior to the current window.  If the specified window is was not active prior to the current window, a logical false is returned.

You can also determine the window that was active prior to the current window with WLAST().

<window name> 
	To determine if a specific window was active prior to the current window, include the window's name in WLAST().

	If a <window name> is not included in WLAST(), the name of the window which was active prior to the current window is returned.  If the window you specify in WLAST() does not exist, false is returned.



