	Enter legitimate file name or any portion of file name combined with wildcard characters.  Include more than one file specification by separating specifications with semicolon.

[ ] Specify text to search for...
	Brings forward Specify Text dialog to enter text strings to find.  When checked, text strings have been entered.

[ ] Search subdirectories
	When checked, finds files that meet specifications in current directory and its subdirectories.



See Also:  Filer, Specify Text

",Interface di me
 Format,"
             Format              

This dialog, displayed from the Report Expression dialog, allows you to format your field expressions.  The following are the formatting options available for each database field type:

() Character 
	[ ] Alpha Only
		When checked, allows only alphabetic characters.

	[ ] To Upper Case
		When checked, converts all characters to uppercase.

	[ ] R
		When checked, displays non-format characters but not stored.

	[ ] Edit ""SET"" Date
		When checked, edits data as date using current SET DATE format.

	[ ] British Date
		When checked, edits data as European (BRITISH) date.

	[ ] Trim
		When checked, removes all leading and trailing blank spaces.

	[ ] Right Align
		When checked, prints data flush right in field.

	[ ] Center
		When checked, centers data in field.

	[ ] Select on Entry
		When checked, selects entire field when cursor enters field (not available in reports).

( ) Numeric Data
	[ ] Left Justify
		When checked, all numeric data for field begins at leftmost position in field.

	[ ] Blank if Zero
		When checked, field is blank if output is 0.

	[ ] (Negative)
		When checked, places negative numbers in parentheses.

	[ ] Edit ""SET"" Date
		When checked, edits data as date using current SET DATE format.

	[ ] British Date
		When checked, edits data as European (BRITISH) date.

	[ ] CR if Positive
		When checked, CR (credit) appears after number if number is positive.

	[ ] DB if Negative
		When checked, DB (debit) appears after number if number is negative.

	[ ] Leading Zeros
		When checked, prints all leading zeros.

	[ ] Currency
		When checked, displays currency format.

	[ ] Scientific
		When checked, displays in scientific notation.

	[ ] Select on Entry
		When checked, selects entire field when cursor enters field (not available in reports).

( ) Date Data
	[ ] Edit ""SET"" Date
		When checked, edits data as  date using current SET DATE format.

	[ ] British Date
		When checked, edits data as European (BRITISH) date.

	[ ] Select on Entry
		When checked, selects entire field when cursor enters field (not available in reports).

( ) Logical Data
	[ ] Select on Entry
		When checked, selects entire field when cursor enters field (not available in reports).


           Format Codes          
 
 
Format  

You may enter the following format codes:

	A	Displays only alphabetic characters.

	K	Selects entire field when cursor enters field.

	L	Displays logical data only.

	N	Displays letters and digits only.

	X	Displays any character.

	9	Displays digits only for character data.  Displays digits and signs for numeric data.

	#	Displays digits, blanks and signs.

	$	Displays fixed dollar sign in front of numeric value.

	$$	Displays floating dollar sign in front of numeric value.

	*	Displays asterisks in front of the numeric value (used in combination with $ for check protection).

	.	Specifies decimal point position.

	,	Separates digits left of the decimal point.

	@;	In reports only, forces a line feed in an expression in the Detail band of a report.  



See Also:  Expression Builder, Report Expression, Report Writer, Screen Builder, Screen Field

