There are two versions of the Generate Screen dialog.  One version appears when you choose Generate on the Program menu popup, the other version appears when you add a screen set to a project.  The options in these dialogs are:  

Screen Set (list)
	Displays screens to be generated into one program file.  To change order of screens, click on double-headed arrow and drag or select screen and press Ctrl+PgUp or Ctrl+PgDn.  Double-click on screen name to modify screen.

< Edit >
	Displays Screen Design window for selected screen.

< Add >
	Displays Add Screen dialog.
	
< Remove >
	Removes selected screen from screen set.

< Arrange >
	Allows you to arrange screens on the monitor for generation purposes only.

Code Options
	This section of the Generate dialog allows you to specify whether or not specific code segments will be automatically generated.

[X] Open Files
	When checked, code is generated to open databases and indexes, and to set up relations.

[X] Close Files
	When checked, code is generated to close all files upon completion of generated program.

[X] Define Windows
	When checked, windows are automatically defined in the generated program using the information specified in Screen Layout dialog.

[X] Release Windows
	When checked, RELEASE WINDOW statements are generated.

[X] READ CYCLE
	When checked, READ CYCLE is generated in the program.

[ ] Multiple READs
	When checked, a READ command is generated between the format statements for each screen panel.

[ ] READ NOLOCK
	When checked, a NOLOCK clause is generated with READ command.  Available in FoxPro/LAN.

[ ] MODAL
	When checked, a MODAL clause is generated with READ command.

[ ] Associated Windows...
	When checked, brings forward Associated Windows dialog.

< Output Options... > 

	(in dialog accessed through Generate on Program menu popup)
	Allows entry of path and file name for output file, or choose  Output Options push button to bring forward Save As dialog.

Screen Set Name
< Output File... >

	(in dialog accessed through Project Manager)
	Allows entry of name for screen set to be included in project.

< Comment Options... >
	Brings forward the Comment Options dialog.



See Also:  Add Screen, Associated Window, Comment Options, Debug, Menu Builder, Open File, Project, Save As, Screen Builder, Screen Layout, Trace

