 Hot Keys,"
             Hot Keys            

When defining push buttons, radio buttons and check boxes, you may define hot keys associated with the prompts by placing \< before the letter of the prompt that will be the hot key.",Interface
 Index,"
              Index              

This option creates compound or single entry indexes.  A compound index is an index that contains any number of separate index entries or tags.  All tags in a compound index are available when the file is opened.  A single entry index is limited to one index entry.  Non-compact single entry indexes should be created only if you need to maintain compatibility with older version of FoxPro (prior to FoxPro 2.0) or if you're sharing data with FoxBASE+ or FoxBASE+/Mac.

This dialog contains these options:

Database Fields: (list)
	Displays fields of active database.

Options

() Ascending
	Sorts fields in ascending order.

( ) Descending
	Sorts fields in descending order.	

[ ] Unique
	When checked, displays only unique fields of specified field(s).
	
< For... > 
	Displays Expression Builder to create a For clause.

Tag name 
	Type in the name of the tag.
	
< Move > 
	Places tag in Index Expression scrollable list.

< Remove/Edit >
	Removes tag from Index On scrollable list.
	
Index On: (list)
	Lists all index tags or expressions.

Index Expression 
< Expr... >



	Type in expression in text box or choose Expr to display the Expression Builder to create index expression.

Output

() IDX 
	Creates .IDX index.
	
[X] Compact 
	When checked, creates a compact .IDX index.
	
( ) CDX 
	Creates a .CDX index.
	
[X] Structural 
	When checked, creates a structural .CDX index.
	
< Save As... > 

	Type in name of index or choose Save As to display a Save As dialog.
	


See Also:  Expression Builder, New File

