",Interface di me
 Label Designer,"
          Label Designer         

Labels are defined in the Label Layout window.  The default layout for the Label Layout window is 3-1/2"" x 5/16"" x 1.  The Layout window contains the following options allowing you to change the layout:

Remarks 
	Enter a description of the layout.  This description appears in the Layout menu popup if you save the layout. 

Margin 
	Enter the left margin in columns.

Width  
	Enter the width of the label in columns.

Number Across 
	Enter the number of labels across the page.

Height 
	Enter the height of the label in rows.

Spaces Between 
	Enter the spaces between labels across a page.

 Lines Between 
	Enter the lines between each label.

When the Label Layout window is active, a Label menu popup appears on the system menu bar.  This menu popup contains the following options:

Page Preview... 
	Display labels in Page Preview window.

Expression...
	Brings forward Expression Builder to define expression for label.  Alternately, you can type the expression directly into the definition area.  Any text in the label definition must be enclosed in quotation marks. 

Environment...
	Brings forward Label Environment dialog.

Style...
	Brings forward Style dialog.  You can define a style for each line in a label definition. 
	
Add Alias
	Toggle option that places alias with all defined fields.

Layout
	Displays popup with all defined layouts.

Save Layout...
	Brings forward Save Layout dialog.

Delete Layout...
	Brings forward Delete Layout dialog.

A label can include database field information, calculated fields and computed fields.  You can use the Expression Builder to build and verify each line in the label, or you can type expressions on each line of the text box in the Label Layout window.



See Also:  Delete Layout, Expression Builder, Label Environment, New File, Open File, Page Preview, Save As

