In the Menu Design window, you can design or modify a menu system.

To define a menu system:
	Prompt
		
	Enter prompt name.  

	To change the order of items in a list with double-headed arrows (), press Tab until the item you wish to move is selected.  Press Ctrl+PgUp or Ctrl+PgDn to move the item up or down in the list.

	Mouse users can click on the double-headed arrow and drag the item to the desired location in the list.

	Choose result from Result popup.  Options in this popup are:
		Submenu	
			To create submenu for pad or option.  Create push button appears.  Choose to bring forward Design window to define submenu.

		Command	 
			To define command for pad or option.  Text box appears.  Enter command in text box.

		Pad Name/Bar#  
			Pad Name appears when defining pads, Bar# appears when defining submenu options.  Text box appears.  Enter pad name or Bar# in text box.

		Proc.
			To define procedure of pad or option.  Create  push button appears.  Choose Create to launch editing window for procedure.

	Options [ ]
		Choosing this check box brings forward Prompt Options dialog.

< Try It > 
	Defined menu system is displayed.  Choose option to display Try It dialog with prompt information. 

< Insert > 
< Delete > 
	Inserts or deletes menu pad or submenu option.

