",Interface di me
 Pack,"
              Pack               

Permanently removes from database all records marked for deletion.  There is no way to recover deleted records after the database has been packed.",Interface me
 Page Layout,"
           Page Layout           

The Page Layout dialog allows you to define where on the page a report is printed and save environment information.  This dialog contains the following options: 

Page length  (rows):  
	Enter number of lines to appear on each page of report.

Top margin   (rows):   
	Enter number of blank lines to appear at top of each page of report.

Bottom margin (rows): 
	Enter number of blank lines to appear at bottom of each page of report.

Printer indent (columns):  
	Enter number of characters indented from left edge of printed page.

Right margin column: 
	Enter number of columns across the page for printed output.

	Example:
		The maximum number of columns on a printed page for the type style you are using is 80.

		You want a report to print 70 characters across the page with a 5 column margin on each side of the page.

		You would set the printer indent to five, and the right margin column to 70.

< Options... >
	Brings forward Report Print Options dialog.

Environment:
< Save >   <Restore>   <Clear>
	To save, restore or clear environment information.
	
[ ] Printer Driver Setup... 
	Brings forward Printer Driver Setup dialog allowing you to define a printer driver setup that is saved with the report definition.  When checked, a printer driver setup has been defined.



See Also:  Page Layout Options, Report Writer

",Interface di me
 Page Layout Options,"
