",Interface di me
 Preferences,"
          Preferences            

Text editor, Calculator and Expression Builder each have preferences.

Text Editor Preferences
	Enabled when text, program or memo window is active.

This dialog contains these options:

[X] Wrap words
	When checked, wraps text in current window to next line when it reaches right margin.  By default, this check box is checked for text files and memo fields and unchecked for program files.

[X] Auto indent 
	When checked, indents line by same amount as previous line.

[X] Make backup
	When checked, stores previous version of edited file or program as backup.

[X] Add line feeds
	When checked, saves files or programs using a carriage return and line feed at end of all lines.

[ ] Status line
	When checked, displays status line at top of text editing area.  

[ ] Compile when saved 
	When checked, instructs FoxPro to compile program after it is saved.  This check box is available for program files only.

[ ] Ctrl-Z sensitive
	When checked, instructs FoxPro to stop reading file or program when it encounters Ctrl+Z.

() Left justify
	Aligns all text at left edge of editing window.

( ) Right justify
	Aligns all text at right edge of editing window.

( ) Center justify
	Centers each line of text in window.

Tab size: 
	Sets distance (in number of spaces) that cursor advances when Tab key is pressed.  

[ ] Use these preferences
	When checked, designates all settings should be used as defaults with new text, program or memo windows.

[ ] Save preference 
	When checked, stores preference settings in  resource file so each time file is opened, it appears as it was left at end of last editing session.

Calculator Preferences
	Enabled when Calculator is active.

This dialog contains these options:

() Don't alter NumLock 
	Invokes calculator without affecting state of NumLock.

( ) Remember NumLock State 
	Causes Calculator to remember and revert to state of NumLock at last time it was used.

( ) Force NumLock ON 
	Turns NumLock on when Calculator is activated.

() Automatic 
	Displays calculated results based on number of decimal places in numbers entered and operation performed.

( ) Floating 
	Displays numbers to highest degree of precision.

( ) Fixed 
	Type number of decimal places to appear in all values, both entered and calculated.

Expression Builder Preferences
	Enabled when Expression Builder is active.

This dialog contains these options:

() Math 
	Choose to adjust options that appear in Math menu popup.

( ) String
	Choose to adjust options that appear in String menu popup.

( ) Logical 
	Choose to adjust options that appear in Logical menu popup.

Functions (List)
	Displays menu popup options corresponding to selected radio button.  A bullet appears to the left of all functions that are displayed in the popup.

	Select a function in the list and double-click (with the mouse or the Spacebar) to toggle the bullet on and off.

< All >
	Places leading bullet next to each option and adds all options to popup.

< Clear >
	Removes leading bullets next to all options and removes them from popup.

() Always add alias
	Instructs FoxPro to use database name to create expression.

( ) Add non-selected alias only 
	Instructs FoxPro to include name of database not in selected work area to create relational expression.

( ) Never add alias 
	Instructs FoxPro to omit database name to create expression.

[ ] Show System Memory Variable 
	When checked, displays/removes system memory variables from Expression Builder.



See Also:  Calculator, Expression Builder, Text Editing

