 RQBE,"
               RQBE              

Displays RQBE window to modify or create a query.

This window contains these options:

Database (List)
	Displays all databases included in query.

< Add >
	Displays Open File dialog to open a database to include in query.

< Clear >
	Closes selected database.
	
Output Fields... (List)
	Displays fields to be output in query in order they appear in list. 

	To change the order of items in a list with double-headed arrows (), press Tab until the item you wish to move is selected.  Press Ctrl+PgUp or Ctrl+PgDn to move the item up or down in the list.

	Mouse users can click on the double-headed arrow and drag the item to the desired location in the list.

[ ] Select Fields...
	Displays Select Fields dialog.  When checked, fields have been specified.
	
[ ] Order By...
	Displays Order By dialog.  When checked, an order has been specified.
	
[ ] Group By...
	Displays Group By check box.  When checked, a group has been specified.
	
[ ] Having...
	Displays Having dialog.  When checked, a having clause has been specified.


 Output To 

 	Choose one of following output options:  Browse, Report/Label, Table/DBF, Cursor, Graph.


	Enabled when Table/DBF, Cursor, or Graph chosen from popup.  Type in file name and path for output file.

[ ] Options
	Only enabled when Report/Label appears on Output To popup control.  Displays RQBE Display Options dialog.  When checked, options have been specified.

Field Name
 (Popup)
	Choose field to set comparison.  If expression... chosen, Expression Builder is displayed.

NOT
[ ]
	When checked, inverses condition.

Condition  (Popup)
	Choose a condition.  By default, ""Like"" is displayed on this popup.

Example

	Type in comparison text.

UpLo
[ ]
	When checked, ignores capitalization of character data.

< Insert >
	Inserts new condition above selected condition.

< Remove >
	Deletes selected condition.

< Or >
	Creates an OR condition.

< See SQL >
	Displays read-only window containing SQL SELECT command.

< Do Query >
	Performs created query.

Comments... menu option
	Displays Comment dialog.
	


See Also:  Comment, New File, Open File, RQBE Display Options, RQBE Group By, RQBE Having, RQBE Join Condition, RQBE Order By, RQBE Select Fields

