",Interface di
 RQBE Select Fields,"
       RQBE Select Fields        

RQBE Select Fields allows you to specify fields, functions and expressions to include in a query, adjust order of field appearance, remove fields and eliminate duplicate entries using these controls:

Database Fields (List)
	Double-click on field, or select field then choose Move push button to move it to Selected Output list.

Selected Output (List)
	Double-click on field, or select field then choose Remove push button to remove it from Selected Output list.  

	To change the order of items in a list with double-headed arrows (), press Tab until the item you wish to move is selected.  Press Ctrl+PgUp or Ctrl+PgDn to move the item up or down in the list.

	Mouse users can click on the double-headed arrow and drag the item to the desired location in the list.

< Move  >
	Moves selected field from Database Fields list to Selected Output list.

< All  >
	Moves all fields from Database Fields list to Selected Output list.

< Remove >
	Removes selected field from Selected Output list.

< Remove All >
	Deletes all fields from Selected Output list.


 Functions  

	Choose function to include in output and then choose Move push button.


	Type in function to include in output and then choose Move push button.

[ ] No Duplicates
	When checked, removes records in which all fields match.

[ ] Cross Tabulate
	To output query results to FoxGraph, a report form or a table in cross tabular format, check Cross Tabulate.  Cross Tabulate is only enabled when you have exactly three items selected in the RQBE Select Fields dialog.  These three items represent the X axis, the Y axis and the cell value for the graph.

	For example, if you want to generate a clients report that shows the amount billed to them by month for one year, you could create a graph that displays clients down the left side of the page, January-December across the top of the page and graphs the amount billed to each client each month.

	In the RQBE window, add CUSTOMER.DBF and INVOICES.DBF, joined on CNO.  In the RQBE Select Fields dialog, choose COMPANY, DAY(INV.IDATE) and INV.ITOTAL.  Check Cross Tabulate and choose OK.  In the RQBE window, make sure Browse shows on the Output To popup control then Do Query.



See Also:  RQBE

