 Structure,"
            Structure            

This dialog allows you to define or modify structure of a database.

The Structure dialog contains these options:

Field 
	Enter field name (up to 10 characters beginning with a letter or underscore) below Name heading.   

	To change the order of items in a list with double-headed arrows (), press Tab until the item you wish to move is selected.  Press Ctrl+PgUp or Ctrl+PgDn to move the item up or down in the list.

	Mouse users can click on the double-headed arrow and drag the item to the desired location in the list.

Type  (popup)
	Specify data type (Character, Numeric, Float, Date, Logical or Memo).

Width 
	Specify width of field.  

	Data Type	Width in Characters
	
	Character	10-254
	Numeric		1-20, including optional plus/minus sign and decimal place
	Date 		8
	Logical		1
	Memo 		10
	Float		1-20, including optional plus/minus sign and decimal place

< Insert >
	Choose to insert new field before selected field.

< Delete >
	Choose to remove selected field from database structure.

Adding/Removing Structural Compound Index Tags
	Position cursor in shaded area directly preceding field.  Double-click mouse or press Spacebar once to toggle between ascending, descending, or removing index tag.

Structure menu popup is provided specifically for keyboard users.  Keyboard users need to use options or control key shortcuts from popup instead of Insert and Delete push buttons.



See Also:  Append, New File, Setup

