 Style,"
             Style               

Selections made in the Style dialog cause the printed output to appear with the specified Style attributes.

[ ] Bold
[ ] Italic
[ ] Underline
[ ] Superscript
[ ] Subscript
	Checking one of these options causes the associated Style code to appear in the text box at the bottom of the Style dialog.  The style is applied to the object (in a report) or line (in a label) when you print.  

	You can check more than one check box.  If you check an option that excludes another option, the excluded option is dimmed.

() Left
( ) Center
( ) Right
	For use with non-proportional fonts, these radio buttons allow you to specify the alignment (left justified, centered or right justified) of text in a field (in a report) or on a line (in a label).

Code 
	You can enter style codes in the this text box.  If your printer driver supports style codes other than those available with FoxPro printer drivers, you can enter these style codes in the text box.

Selected styles and alignments appear in printed output only and are not reflected in the Report Layout window, Label Design window or Page Preview window.  For selected styles to appear in printed output, your printer must support the styles.



